</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59); font-weight: bold;">##</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(184, 10, 24); font-weight: bold;"> 🇬🇧 About</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span>Nautilus is a </span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">federation protocol</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span> and reference implementation 
</span></span><span>for independent git repositories containing knowledge in different 
</span><span>native formats, without forcing them into a unified schema.
</span><span>
</span><span><span>Just as an Office Suite reads </span><span class="token token code-snippet code" style="color: rgb(129, 0, 194);">`.docx`</span><span>, </span><span class="token token code-snippet code" style="color: rgb(129, 0, 194);">`.pdf`</span><span>, and </span><span class="token token code-snippet code" style="color: rgb(129, 0, 194);">`.xlsx`</span><span> without 
</span></span><span>merging them into one format — Nautilus reads repositories in an 
</span><span>ecosystem, finds bridges between them, and builds a common search 
</span><span>layer on top.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59); font-weight: bold;">###</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(184, 10, 24); font-weight: bold;"> Philosophy</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span>Most modern knowledge systems (Notion, Obsidian, Roam, Coda) 
</span><span>require migrating data into their unified format. This creates 
</span><span>vendor lock-in, erases authorial models, and homogenizes different 
</span><span>types of knowledge.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Nautilus takes the opposite path:</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Each repository keeps its native format
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Translation between formats happens through adapters, on demand
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Consensus is computed as intersection of results across repos
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Adding a new repository takes 5 minutes and requires no 
</span></span><span>  refactoring
