</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59); font-weight: bold;">##</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(184, 10, 24); font-weight: bold;"> 1. Problem Statement</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59); font-weight: bold;">###</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(184, 10, 24); font-weight: bold;"> 1.1. The Paradox of Abundant Demand and Underutilized Supply</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span>The AI industry in 2026 exhibits an apparent paradox. Frontier 
</span><span>labs simultaneously report unprecedented demand for senior 
</span><span>technical talent and unprecedented labor shortages. As of 
</span><span>April 2026:
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> </span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Anthropic</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>: 440 open positions, primarily senior roles at 
</span></span><span>  $320K–$405K compensation
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> </span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">OpenAI</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>: estimated 600+ open positions
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> </span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Google DeepMind</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>: estimated 400+ open positions
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> </span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Mistral, Cohere, Inflection, xAI</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>: collectively 1000+ open 
</span></span><span>  positions
</span><span>
</span><span>Total unmet senior-level demand in AI companies alone exceeds 
</span><span>2,500 positions globally. Existing recruiting pipelines close 
</span><span>perhaps 100-200 of these positions monthly across the industry.
</span><span>
</span><span>Simultaneously, substantial populations of qualified knowledge 
</span><span>workers remain outside this hiring pipeline through no deficiency 
</span><span>in skill or motivation. We estimate this pool contains 
</span><span>approximately:
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> </span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">500,000+ retired professionals</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span> globally with relevant 
</span></span><span>  technical expertise and available time, in OECD countries alone
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> </span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">5M+ disabled specialists</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span> with intact intellectual capacity 
</span></span><span>  but modified work requirements
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> </span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Unknown but substantial</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span> population of domain experts 
</span></span><span>  (lawyers, doctors, educators) with demonstrable AI interest 
</span><span>  but no CS credentials
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> </span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Millions</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span> of geographically-dispersed skilled workers in 
</span></span><span>  regions without direct hire access to frontier AI companies
</span><span>
</span><span>These populations are not mutually exclusive and together 
</span><span>represent talent resource orders of magnitude larger than 
</span><span>current unmet demand.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">The failure is not of supply and demand. The failure is of 
</span></span><span><span class="token token bold content">matching infrastructure.</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59); font-weight: bold;">###</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(184, 10, 24); font-weight: bold;"> 1.2. Why This Matters Beyond Economics</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span>Unemployment or underemployment of qualified elders and 
</span><span>disabled experts is not merely economic inefficiency. It 
</span><span>produces measurable harms:
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> </span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Individual harms</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>: loss of professional identity, social 
</span></span><span>  isolation, declining cognitive engagement, depression
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> </span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Family harms</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>: reduced contribution to household economics, 
</span></span><span>  increased caregiving burden
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> </span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Societal harms</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>: loss of accumulated tacit knowledge, 
</span></span><span>  weakening of intergenerational transmission, reduced civic 
</span><span>  participation
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> </span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">AI safety harms</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>: narrower perspective pool in AI 
</span></span><span>  development, reduced diversity in alignment research, 
</span><span>  concentration of AI power in demographically homogeneous groups
</span><span>
</span><span>The last point is particularly relevant for foundation missions. 
</span><span>Beneficial AI requires diverse human input. Current pipelines 
</span><span>systematically exclude several high-value perspective sources.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59); font-weight: bold;">###</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(184, 10, 24); font-weight: bold;"> 1.3. Why Now</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span>Three trends converge to make this infrastructure newly feasible:
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">First</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>, AI capabilities (particularly LLM-based assistants 
</span></span><span>like Claude, GPT-4, Gemini) crossed a threshold in 2024-2025 
</span><span>enabling genuine coordination of distributed knowledge work 
</span><span>previously requiring collocation. The Model Context Protocol 
</span><span>(MCP) released by Anthropic in late 2024 provides standardized 
</span><span>substrate for AI-assisted workflows.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Second</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>, employment models are shifting: classic full-time 
</span></span><span>permanent employment covers declining fraction of knowledge 
</span><span>work. 36% of US workers engage in freelance/contract work in 
</span><span>2026, up from 27% in 2020. Foundation-funded dignified alternatives 
</span><span>become newly viable.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Third</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>, regulatory frameworks are catching up: EU Platform 
</span></span><span>Work Directive (2024), EU AI Act (2024), various national 
</span><span>initiatives recognize digital labor as policy concern. 
</span><span>Infrastructure built now can shape future regulation rather 
</span><span>than adapting to it.
</span><span>
</span><span>This is not a future problem requiring speculative solutions. 
</span><span>It is a present problem with actionable solutions that require 
</span><span>coordinated action now.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token hr" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">---</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59); font-weight: bold;">##</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(184, 10, 24); font-weight: bold;"> 2. Target Populations</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59); font-weight: bold;">###</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(184, 10, 24); font-weight: bold;"> 2.1. Retired Experts with Remaining Intellectual Capacity</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Size estimate</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>: 500K+ in OECD countries with relevant skills 
</span></span><span>for knowledge work.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Characteristics</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>:
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Decades of domain expertise
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Reduced but significant work capacity (15-25 hours/week 
</span></span><span>  typical)
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Modest income supplementation preferred over full salary
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Value meaning, mentorship, intellectual engagement
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Often excluded from tech roles due to age bias
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Unique value proposition from OKWF</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>:
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Dignified part-time engagement
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Mentorship opportunities for younger contributors
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> AI assistance mitigating technical skill obsolescence
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Identity continuity with professional life
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Example use cases</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>:
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Retired German law professor contributing to legal pattern 
</span></span><span>  library and junior legal writer mentorship
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Former medical researcher reviewing bioinformatics code
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Retired journalist leading science communication guild
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59); font-weight: bold;">###</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(184, 10, 24); font-weight: bold;"> 2.2. Disabled Specialists with Modified Work Requirements</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Size estimate</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>: 5M+ in OECD countries with preserved 
</span></span><span>intellectual capacity and specific support needs.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Characteristics</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>:
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Technical expertise often comparable to non-disabled peers
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Variable daily capacity (good days and bad days)
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Need flexibility impossible in most full-time roles
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Often experience employment discrimination
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Frequently have direct relevant experience (e.g., disability 
</span></span><span>  rights advocacy)
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Unique value proposition from OKWF</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>:
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Asynchronous work accommodating variable capacity
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> No discrimination in selection (AI-assisted blind matching)
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Bringing disability-informed perspective to beneficial AI
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Direct expertise in accessibility research
</span></span><span>
