</span></span><span>
</span><span>OKWF is not and will not become a for-profit entity. Operational 
</span><span>sustainability comes from:
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">1.</span><span> </span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Core endowment</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span> from foundational corporate partners and 
</span></span><span>   foundation grants (€3-8M initial, growing to €50M+ target)
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">2.</span><span> </span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Grant funding</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span> for specific initiatives and research (€1-3M 
</span></span><span>   annually)
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">3.</span><span> </span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Earned revenue</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span> from commercial projects routed through 
</span></span><span>   platform (growing to majority of operational funding over 
