</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59); font-weight: bold;">###</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(184, 10, 24); font-weight: bold;"> 6.1. Governance Structure</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Board of Directors</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span> (7 members):
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> 2 corporate partners (rotating)
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> 2 foundation representatives (Mozilla-type)
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> 2 contributor representatives (elected by contributors)
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> 1 independent (academic or public policy)
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Executive team</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span> (3-5 people):
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Executive Director
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Technical Director
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Community Director
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Legal Director
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Guild councils</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>: Each guild has elected 3-person council 
</span></span><span>governing internal affairs.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Contributor assembly</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>: Annual gathering of all contributors 
</span></span><span>with binding decisional authority on specified matters 
</span><span>(stipend minimums, dignity standards, guild boundaries).
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59); font-weight: bold;">###</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(184, 10, 24); font-weight: bold;"> 6.2. Key Ethical Commitments</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Commitment 1</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>: No contributor will be charged fees or 
</span></span><span>subjected to rent-seeking. Foundation takes 0% from contributor 
</span><span>earnings.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Commitment 2</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>: Contributor intellectual property remains 
</span></span><span>with contributor by default. Specific projects may transfer 
</span><span>rights with transparent, negotiated terms.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Commitment 3</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>: Anonymization of contributed patterns is 
</span></span><span>voluntary; contributor always retains attribution right.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Commitment 4</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>: No algorithmic management. AI assists 
</span></span><span>coordination but final decisions about contributors remain 
</span><span>with humans.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Commitment 5</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>: Private data (contributors' personal 
</span></span><span>circumstances, health information) remains with contributor. 
</span><span>Foundation handles compliance through delegation, not data 
</span><span>accumulation.
</span><span>
