</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Override governance decisions
</span></span><span>
</span><span>Contributors' sponsors contribute capital but receive only:
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Anonymized patterns (public)
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Transparency reports (aggregated)
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> Brand association (opt-in)
</span></span><span><span></span><span class="token token list" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">-</span><span> First-look invitations to collaborative projects (not guarantees)
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59); font-weight: bold;">###</span><span class="token token title" style="color: rgb(184, 10, 24); font-weight: bold;"> 6.4. Regulatory Compliance</span><span>
</span></span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">GDPR</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span> (EU): Foundation operates as data controller for 
</span></span><span>minimal required personal data. Pattern library governed by 
</span><span>GDPR Article 89 (scientific/statistical research) where 
</span><span>appropriate. Contributor data sovereignty preserved.
</span><span>
</span><span><span></span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span class="token token bold content">Employment law</span><span class="token token bold" style="color: rgb(43, 48, 59);">**</span><span>: Foundation-contributor relationship 
</span></span><span>structured as contractor/grantee, not employment. Compliance 
</span><span>with each jurisdiction's requirements (consulting tax law 
